<item>
            <title>[GROOVY-3685] Printing script causes the editor font to change</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-3685</link>
                <project id="12318123" key="GROOVY">Groovy</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;If you click the Print menu option from inside the Groovy Console, it causes the font in the editor to change&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;And writes:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;2009-08-19 15:28:19.884 java[1597:613] Error loading /Library/Printers/hp/PDEs/hpPostScriptPDE.plugin/Contents/MacOS/hpPostScriptPDE:  dlopen(/Library/Printers/hp/PDEs/hpPostScriptPDE.plugin/Contents/MacOS/hpPostScriptPDE, 265): no suitable image found.  Did find:
	/Library/Printers/hp/PDEs/hpPostScriptPDE.plugin/Contents/MacOS/hpPostScriptPDE: no matching architecture in universal wrapper
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;to the command line&lt;/p&gt;</description>
