                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="14467435" author="tim_yates" created="Thu, 20 Aug 2009 02:25:07 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Actually, this could be an HP driver issue on OS X, causing the Java Print to crash and the font change being a side effect of this crash&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14467653" author="guillaume" created="Thu, 3 Sep 2009 11:45:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve got the same issue, the font becomes Arial, or something like that.&lt;br/&gt;
Changing back the font size brings the original font though.&lt;br/&gt;
I&apos;ve also got an HP printer, and I&apos;m also on OS X.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14467626" author="tim_yates" created="Thu, 3 Sep 2009 12:05:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Could be related to this:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://lists.apple.com/archives/Java-dev/2008/Jan/msg00262.html&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://lists.apple.com/archives/Java-dev/2008/Jan/msg00262.html&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14467598" author="guillaume" created="Thu, 3 Sep 2009 14:16:40 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;But it doesn&apos;t really give the solution to our problem, does it?&lt;br/&gt;
We just call a print job, and we don&apos;t do much more, nowhere where we set the font or anything (beside in the console that is).&lt;br/&gt;
Am I missing something?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14467643" author="tim_yates" created="Fri, 4 Sep 2009 06:35:57 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;After looking into it, it seems to be because the font in the PRINT_PANE is not set to the same as in the actual component, and this causes corruption to the font in the Document object somehow&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I didn&apos;t even know it was recommended to use the same Document in 2 separate components&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The attached diff seems to fix the font changing, but not the HP Driver exception or the fact that you need to CTRL-C the console after printing as Quit no longer works (I guess due to the exception)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
